{"questionId":"2967024","questionHtml":"<p>Determine the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> at which it occurs.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Consideration of graph or table of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mi>n</mi></mfrac></mfenced><mi>n</mi></msup></math> including values either side of 7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>Maximum occurs when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>20</mn><mn>7</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>7</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>1550</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>1554</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>260</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)A0A1</strong></em> for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>7</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>20</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>1570</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2967024","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.2g","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Determine the value of P(20) and the value of n at which it occurs.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"g","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.2—Functions, notation domain, range and inverse as reflection"],"memberSecti